quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  25,3,"Yet people have taken, instead of Him, other deities; those that create nothing but are themselves created; who do not have the power to hurt or benefit even themselves; who have no power over death, nor over life, nor over the resurrection of the dead."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  25,4,"Those who disbelieve in the Message of the Prophet say: "This (Criterion) is nothing but a lie which he has forged with the help of others." Such have indeed resorted to a grievous wrong and sheer falsehood."{1},footnotes:1:1
  25,5,"They say: "These are merely fairy tales of the ancients which he has got inscribed and they are then recited to him morning and evening.""
  25,6,"Say to them (O Muhammad): "It is He Who knows the secrets of the heavens and the earth Who has sent down this Book. Indeed, He is Most Forgiving, Most Compassionate.""{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  25,7,"They say: "What sort of a Messenger is this: he eats food and walks about in the markets? Why was an angel not sent down to him so that he may remain with the Messenger and warn those that do not believe in him?"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  25,8,"Why was a treasure not bestowed upon him, or a garden whereof he might obtain his sustenance?" The evil-doers say: "You are simply following a bewitched man.""{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  25,9,"See what specious arguments they put forth before you: they are so strayed that they will not find their way to anything sound."{1},footnotes:1:1
  25,10,"Most blessed is He Who, if He wills, can grant you even better than what they propose: Gardens beneath which rivers flow, and stately mansions."{1},footnotes:1:1